<FrameLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context="admin.example.com.SubTopics.Prob.BALLS">

    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:focusable="false"
        android:visibility="visible">


        <RelativeLayout
            android:id="@+id/rl1"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginBottom="500dp"
            android:layout_marginEnd="2dp"
            android:layout_marginRight="4dp"
            android:layout_marginTop="30dp"
            android:minHeight="50dp">


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv1"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_toEndOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:layout_toRightOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question  1 :\n
X can do a piece of work in 40 days. He works at it for 8 days and then Y finished it in 16 days.
How long will they together take to complete the work?"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv11"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@+id/tv1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_toEndOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:layout_toRightOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solutions –\n
Work done by X in 8 days = ( 1/40 x 8 ) = 1/5\n

Remaining work = ( 1 - 1/5) = 4/5 	\n

Now, 	4/5 work is done by Y in 16 days.\n

Whole work will be done by Y in ( 16 x 	5/4 ) = 20 days.\n
Therefore X's 1 day's work = 	1/40 	,	 Y's 1 day's work = 1/20	\n

(X + Y)'s 1 day's work = 	( 1/40 + 1/20) 	= 3 /40	\n

Hence, X and Y will together complete the work in 	( 40/3) = 13 1/3 days.
\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121" />

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div1"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv11" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv2"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 2:\n
A and B together can do a piece of work in 30 days.
  A having worked for 16 days, B finishes the remaining work alone in 44 days.
 In how many days shall B finish the whole work alone?

"              android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv22"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv2"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Let A's 1 day's work = x and B's 1 day's work = y.\n

Then, x + y = 	1/30 	and 16x + 44y = 1.\n

Solving these two equations, we get: x = 1/60	and y = 1/60\n

B's 1 day's work = 	1 /60	\n
Hence, B alone shall finish the whole work in 60 days.

\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div2"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv22" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv3"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div2"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 3:\n
4 men and 6 women can complete a work in 8 days, while 3 men and 7 women can complete it in 10 days.
 In how many days will 10 women complete it?
"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv33"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv3"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Let 1 man's 1 day's work = x and 1 woman's 1 day's work = y.\n

Then, 4x + 6y = 1/8 	and 3x + 7y = 1/10\n

Solving the two equations, we get: x = 	11 /400	, y = 	1/400\n

1 woman's 1 day's work = 	1 /400\n

10 women's 1 day's work = (1/400 x 10) = 1/40 	.\n

Hence, 10 women will complete the work in 40 days.
\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div3"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv33" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv4"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div3"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 4.\n
10 women can complete a work in 7 days and 10 children take 14 days to complete the work.
 How many days will 5 women and 10 children take to complete the work? "
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv44"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv4"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
1 woman's 1 day's work = 1/70\n

1 child's 1 day's work = 1/140\n

(5 women + 10 children)'s day's work = 	5/70+ 10/140 = 	1 /14 + 1 /14 = 1/7 \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div4"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv44" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv5"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div4"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 5.\n
P is 30% more efficient than Q. P can complete a work in 23 days.
 If P and Q work together, how much time will it take to complete the same work?
"               android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv55"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv5"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Work done by P in 1 day = 1/23\n

Let work done by Q in 1 day = q\n

q × (130/100) = 1/23\n

=> q = 100/(23×130) = 10/(23×13)\n

Work done by P and Q in 1 day = 1/23 + 10/(23×13) = 23/(23×13)= 1/13
\n
=> P and Q together can do the work in 13 days

 \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div5"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv55" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv6"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div5"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 6.\n
P, Q and R can complete a work in 24, 6 and 12 days respectively.
 The work will be completed in --- days if all of them are working together.
 "
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv66"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv6"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Work done by P in 1 day = 1/24\n

Work done by Q in 1 day = 1/6\n

Work done by R in 1 day = 1/12\n

Work done by P,Q and R in 1 day = 1/24 + 1/6 + 1/12 = 7/24\n

=> Working together, they will complete the work in 24/7 days = 3 3⁄7 days\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div6"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv66" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv7"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div6"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 7.\n
Anil and Suresh are working on a special assignment.
Anil needs 6 hours to type 32 pages on a computer and Suresh needs 5 hours to type 40 pages.
If both of them work together on two different computers, how much time is needed to type an assignment of 110 pages?
"                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv77"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv7"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Pages typed by Anil in 1 hour = 32/6 = 16/3\n

Pages typed by Suresh in 1 hour = 40/5 = 8\n

Pages typed by Anil and Suresh in 1 hour = 16/3 + 8 = 40/3\n

Time taken to type 110 pages when Anil and Suresh work together = 110 × 3 /40 = 33/4\n

= 8 ¼ hours = 8 hour 15 minutes
\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div7"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv77" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv8"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div7"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 8.\n
Assume that 20 cows and 40 goats can be kept for 10 days for Rs.460.
If the cost of keeping 5 goats is the same as the cost of keeping 1 cow,
what will be the cost for keeping 50 cows and 30 goats for 12 days?
"               android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv88"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv8"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solutions ;\n
Assume that cost of keeping a cow for 1 day = c ,\n
cost of keeping a goat for 1 day = g\n

Cost of keeping 20 cows and 40 goats for 10 days = 460\n

Cost of keeping 20 cows and 40 goats for 1 day = 460/10 = 46\n

=> 20c + 40g = 46\n

=> 10c + 20g = 23 ---(1)\n

Given that 5g = c\n

Hence equation (1) can be written as 10c + 4c = 23 => 14c =23\n

=> c=23/14\n

cost of keeping 50 cows and 30 goats for 1 day\n

= 50c + 30g
\n
= 50c + 6c (substituted 5g = c)\n

= 56 c = 56×23/14\n

= 92\n

Cost of keeping 50 cows and 30 goats for 12 days = 12×92 = 1104.

\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div8"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv88" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv9"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div8"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 9.\n
P can lay railway track between two stations in 16 days. Q can do the same job in 12 days.
 With the help of R, they completes the job in 4 days.
 How much days does it take for R alone to complete the work??"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv99"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv9"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Amount of work P can do in 1 day = 1/16\n

Amount of work Q can do in 1 day = 1/12\n

Amount of work P, Q and R can together do in 1 day = 1/4\n

Amount of work R can do in 1 day = 1/4 - (1/16 + 1/12) = 3/16 – 1/12 = 5/48\n

=> Hence R can do the job on 48/5 days = 9 (3/5) days.\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div9"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv99" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv10"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div9"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 10.\n
P,Q and R together earn Rs.1620 in 9 days. P and R can earn Rs.600 in 5 days.
 Q and R in 7 days can earn Rs.910. How much amount does R can earn per day?
 "                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv100"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv10"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Amount Earned by P,Q and R in 1 day = 1620/9 = 180 ---(1)\n

Amount Earned by P and R in 1 day = 600/5 = 120 ---(2)\n

Amount Earned by Q and R in 1 day = 910/7 = 130 ---(3)\n

(2)+(3)-(1) => Amount Earned by P , Q and 2R in 1 day\n

- Amount Earned by P,Q and R in 1 day = 120+130-180 = 70\n

=>Amount Earned by R in 1 day = 70\n

Total number of ways = 8 × 7 × 6 × 5 × 4 × 3 = 8P6\n\n\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div10"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv100" />


        </RelativeLayout>

    </ScrollView>


</FrameLayout>
